verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Bold shall I stand in that great day;
For who aught to my charge shall lay?
Fully, by Thee, absolved I am
from sin and fear, from guilt and shame.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}This spotless robe the same appears
When ruined nature sinks in years:
No age can change its constant hue;
Its glory is forever new.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}O, let the dead now hear Thy voice;
Now bid Thy banished ones rejoice;
Their beauty this, their glorious dress,
Jesus, Thy blood and righteousness!{/lang-eng}
